  "title": "Quality Engineer (ISO 9001/AS9100/NADCAP, Aerospace)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Ensure adherence to quality standards, regulations, and compliance with government, aviation authorities, and customer requirements.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with customers, vendors, and suppliers to address non-conformances, conduct root cause analysis, and implement corrective actions.</li>\n  <li>Conduct internal audits to assess the quality system, products, and processes (ISO9001, AS9100, NADCAP).</li>\n  <li>Review and update quality procedures and control guidelines regularly.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Mechanical, Aeronautical Engineering or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>At least 5 years of experience with <strong>ISO9001/AS9100 QMS and NADCAP standards.</strong></li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge in <strong>fishbone diagrams, FMEA, and 5-whys analysis.</strong></li>\n  <li>Capable of reading and interpreting technical drawings.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
